## Correcting Einstein: Unifying Gravity and Quantum Coherence

Einstein’s General Relativity needs an extension to integrate **quantum coherence**. 
This equation modifies Einstein’s field equations to account for **information-based gravity**.

\[
G_{\mu\nu} + \Lambda g_{\mu\nu} = \frac{8\pi G}{c^4} T_{\mu\nu} + \alpha \nabla_{\mu} \Psi \nabla_{\nu} \Psi^*
\]

### Explanation:
- **\( G_{\mu\nu} \)**: Einstein’s curvature tensor (spacetime geometry)
- **\( \Lambda g_{\mu\nu} \)**: Cosmological constant (dark energy term)
- **\( T_{\mu\nu} \)**: Energy-momentum tensor (mass-energy distribution)
- **\( \Psi \)**: Quantum wavefunction representing coherence
- **\( \nabla_{\mu} \)**: Covariant derivative tracking coherence changes
- **\( \alpha \)**: Coherence constant linking quantum and classical scales

This equation suggests **gravity is the fundamental information binder**, integrating quantum mechanics and relativity without contradiction.
